Marco Antnio Miranda Tbuas (born 29 October 1976 in Moita, Setbal) is a Portuguese retired footballer who played as a goalkeeper. After entering the club's youth system at age 12, Tbuas made his professional debuts with Vitria Futebol Clube in 199899, spending the vast majority of his career at the Setbal-based outfit as a backup. He did manage 19 first division appearances in 200405, having been previously loaned to lowly Desportivo de Beja, in his first professional year. In July 2008, after 13 years, Tbuas was released by Vitria and joined S.C.U. Torreense in the third level. After a sole campaign, he returned to Alentejo after his experience in Beja, moving to another side in level three, S.C. Mineiro Aljustrelense, and retiring at the end of the season at the age of 33.
